comments: Snell (ATL) reaches in and marginal contact occurs with Doncic's (DAL) right wrist after he momentarily loses control of the ball.
Snell (ATL) brings his arm forward and marginal contact occurs with Doncic's (DAL) side/arm as Doncic backs Snell down.
Doncic (DAL) brings his off-arm toward Snell's (ATL) front and marginal contact occurs as Doncic releases away.
Collins (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) path and absorbs the contact.
Collins (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in Brunson's (DAL) path and absorbs the contact.
Collins (ATL) catches the pass prior to the ball entering the imaginary cylinder above the rim.
Finney-Smith (DAL) rests his forearm on Collins' (ATL) backside and marginal contact occurs as Collins catches the pass and completes the alley-oop attempt.
Collins (ATL) and Cauley-Stein (DAL) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Snell (ATL) and Doncic (DAL) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Snell (ATL) moves towards Brunson (DAL) and marginal body contact occurs at the end of the drive.
Collins (ATL) begins rolling toward the lane and incidental contact occurs with Brunson (DAL) as the defensive switch takes place.
Snell (ATL) and Doncic (DAL) engage and disengage with one another as Doncic moves to set the pick.
Snell (ATL) rests his forearm on Brunson's (DAL) right side and marginal contact occurs during Brunson's driving shot attempt.
Gallinari (ATL) grasps Cauley-Stein's (DAL) left arm and quickly releases as marginal contact occurs during rebounding.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) is drawn toward Young (ATL) on the pump fake and marginal contact occurs with Young's right arm as he is passing.
Brunson (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position during Huerter's (ATL) drive to the basket and marginal contact occurs with Huerter's left arm as he goes up for the shot attempt at the rim.

Huerter (ATL) extends his arm forward and some contact occurs with Doncic's (DAL) head as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Cauley-Stein (DAL) is entitled to a normal step on a screen from behind, which he takes, and which leads to incidental and legal contact between Cauley-Stein and Young (ATL).
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Gallinari's (ATL) arm after the release.
